#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:200
msgid "DNS"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:201
msgid ""
"DNS server selection follows your routing rules: a domain routed directly "
"resolves via the Local DNS, a proxied domain via the Remote DNS. Local and "
"reserved domains always use the on-router resolver."
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:206
msgid "Managed DNS"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:207
msgid ""
"Point dnsmasq at sing-box so all LAN clients are resolved through it. When "
"off, only clients with a hardcoded public resolver are intercepted. Leave on "
"unless you know you need dnsmasq to keep resolving directly."
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:214
msgid "Local DNS"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:216
#, javascript-format
msgid ""
"Resolver for directly-routed traffic and for proxy node hostnames. Pick "
"\"WAN DNS\" to follow the WAN-assigned resolver (currently %s), or type an "
"explicit address."
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:217
msgid ""
"Resolver for directly-routed traffic and for proxy node hostnames. Pick "
"\"WAN DNS\" to follow the WAN-assigned resolver, or type an explicit address."
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:218
msgid "WAN DNS (auto-detected)"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:225
msgid "Remote DNS"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:226
msgid ""
"Resolver for proxied traffic. Leave blank to use Cloudflare DNS-over-TLS "
"(tls://1.1.1.1)."
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:235
msgid "Fake-IP for proxied domains"
msgstr ""

#: htdocs/luci-static/resources/view/prism/settings.js:236
msgid ""
"Resolve every proxied domain to a synthetic IP so routing happens by domain "
"without an upstream DNS round-trip. Directly-routed and local domains always "
"resolve normally."
msgstr ""

